------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Attribution and prior work
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

This software re-implements, on Apple Silicon with local open models, the
methodology described in:

  Juraj Gottweis, Wei-Hung Weng, Alexander Daryin, et al. "Towards an AI
  co-scientist." arXiv:2502.18864 (2025).
  https://arxiv.org/abs/2502.18864
  Official PDF: https://storage.googleapis.com/coscientist_paper/ai_coscientist.pdf

The pipeline structure (generation, reflection, ranking, Elo tournament,
evolution, meta-review, proximity) follows the Python reference implementation:

  The Swarm Corporation. "AI-CoScientist." MIT License.
  https://github.com/The-Swarm-Corporation/AI-CoScientist

The Python reference is built on the Swarms multi-agent framework:

  kyegomez. "Swarms." Apache License 2.0.
  https://github.com/kyegomez/swarms

This project does not include source code from those projects; it is an
independent Swift implementation of the same methodology. The credits above are
provided for academic attribution and acknowledgement.

Note: Google's "AI co-scientist" (cited above) is distinct from Sakana AI's
"The AI Scientist" (arXiv:2408.06292), which is a separate, unrelated system.
